The paper discusses the use of Deep Neural Networks (DNN) for the inversion of borehole resistivity measurements. This involves the use of machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the Computer Science sub-categories of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of image processing techniques to create a layered model of the subsurface, which is associated with the Computer Science sub-category of Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper involves the use of data analysis techniques to process the borehole resistivity measurements, which is associated with the Computer Science sub-category of Data Mining (cs.DM).
